title: beruka_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Beruka[/b] (ベルカ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

She serves under [[Camilla (fire emblem)|]] as a go getting hitwoman. She has an expressionless face and is taciturn, leading her to be a person who projects an inhospitable aura. She joined as Camilla's favorite "strong woman" and thus is her right hand.

She is voiced by Tazawa Masumi in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wyvern Rider

title: hinata_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Hinata[/b] (ヒナタ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

A samurai who serves [[Takumi (fire emblem)|]]. He was born into a samurai clan that has served the Hoshido Royal Family for generations. He's easily fooled and quick to anger, but is extremely quick to befriend and is adept at pulling people together.

He is voiced by Ichiki Mitsuhiro in the Japanese version and by Cam Clarke in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class:[/b] Samurai -> Swordmaster

title: keaton_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Keaton[/b] (フランネル, [i]Flannel[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Keaton is a Wolfskin, capable of turning into werewolf-like creatures. Living on Mount Garou, a Nohrian mountain range, he is the leader of his pack. While well-dressed and fulfilling a leader function, he is extremely messy and not in the least bit concerned with his appearance. He is most attracted to objects out of everyone in the army.

He is voiced by Jun Osuka in the Japanese version and by Gideon Emery in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wolfskin

title: velouria_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Velouria[/b] (ベロア, [i]Velour[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Velouria is the daughter of [[Keaton_(fire_emblem)|]]. She loves everything about her father, to the point that it is almost obsessive. Has the messiest room.

She is voiced by [[Arakawa Miho]] in the Japanese version and by Angela Maria Volpe in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wolfskin

title: kaden_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Kaden[/b] (ニシキ, [i]Nishiki[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

A Kitsune youth who lives in a remote region of Hoshido. Following his father's footsteps, he acts as his clan's leader and keeps his people in order. Very concerned with his appearance, Nishiki is often found grooming himself, so that his fur remains in top condition. He apparently has the best attitude.

He is voiced by Yuuta Takahashi in the Japanese version and by Max Mittelman in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Kitsune

title: percy_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Lutz[/b] (ルッツ, [b]Percy[/b] in the English version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Lutz is the son of [[Arthur_(fire_emblem_fates)|]]. Though his father is perpetually unlucky, Lutz has astronomically good luck.

He is voiced by Tomo Muranaka in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wyvern Rider.

title: ignatius_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Ignatius[/b] (イグニス, [i]Ignis[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Ignatius is the son of [[Benny_(fire_emblem)|]]. Though he looks unsociable at a glance, he is a timid, easily frightened person, much like his father. He is fond of cute things, which he is very shy about.

He is voiced by Akinori Egoshi in the Japanese version and by Kaiji Tang in the English version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Knight

title: karel_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Karel[/b] is a character from [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]] and [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]].

One of few characters who has a playable appearance in both titles, Karel's personality drastically differs between the games. [[Karla (Fire Emblem)|] is his sister, [[Bartre (Fire Emblem)|]] his brother-in-law, and [[Fir (Fire Emblem)|]], his niece.

In [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]], Karel is a bloodthirsty warrior who will stop at nothing to sate his bloodlust, to the point where he is better known by his moniker of [i]Sword Demon[/i]. He can be recruited instead of [[Harken (Fire Emblem)|]] depending on the conditions met during the chapter.

Twenty years later, in [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]], Karel appears as an endgame recruit in Chapter 23, and only Fir and Bartre are capable of recruiting him, convincing Karel to fight alongside his family one more time. Now much older, Karel has significantly calmed down and appears almost as though he were a different person altogether. He serves as a mentor for other characters, and shares a brotherly bond with his brother-in-law Bartre.

Following the end of the Disturbance of Bern, Karel retreats back to his village in Bern, where junior swordfighters learn the path of the sword, guided by his indirect mentoring.

Class: [b]Swordmaster[/b] (both appearances)

title: rinkah_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Rinkah[/b] (リンカ, [i]Rinka[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

She is from the Tribe of Flames, which is an independent group from the Kingdom. Following her father (the chief)'s orders, she moved to assist the Kingdom of Hoshido. In accordance with her tribe’s custom of honoring solitude, she does not interact with her comrades more than is necessary.

She is voiced by [[Ishikawa Yui]] in the Japanese version.

title: hana_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Hana[/b] (カザハナ, [i]Kazahana[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

She serves [[Sakura (fire emblem)|]]. She is one of the best swordsmen in the country, and her father served King Sumeragi. While not of noble birth, Sakura is her liege and best friend since childhood. To protect Sakura, she muddies herself every day while training rigorously.

She is voiced by Sugaya Yayoi in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Samurai -> Swordmaster

title: gunter_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Gunter[/b] (ギュンター Gyuntā) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

A Knight who has served the Kingdom of Nohr for a long time and made his name due to his distinguished military service. He watches over [[corrin (fire emblem)|Corrin]] (the Avatar) during their campaign in a strict yet gentle way.

He is voiced by Nayaru Kurou in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Great Knight

title: arthur_(fire_emblem_fates)
body:

[[Elise (fire emblem)|]]'s subordinate. He crushes evil and protects justice, He's a Hero of Justice, specifically! He has always followed the path of the righteous, all his life, like the waves flow he has obeyed this rule. He has extremely bad luck, which is even reflected in gameplay by his abysmal Luck stat and growth. [spoiler]However, his luck is said to improve in his old age.[/spoiler]

He is voiced by Kitazawa Riki in the Japanese version and by Cam Clarke in the English localization.

title: roulette
body:
A [[casino]] game named after the French word meaning [i]little wheel[/i]. In the game, players may choose to place bets on either a single number or a range of numbers, the colors red or black, or whether the number is odd or even, or if the numbers are high (19-36) or low (1-18)

To determine the winning number and color, a croupier (dealer) spins a wheel in one direction, then spins a ball in the opposite direction around a tilted circular track running around the circumference of the wheel. The ball eventually loses momentum and falls onto the wheel and into one of 37 (in French/European roulette) or 38 (in American roulette) colored and numbered pockets on the wheel. Payouts range from 35:1 for a single number bet down to 1:1 for an odd/even or red/black bet.

h4.See also

* [[roulette table]]

title: atlantic_puffin_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The Atlantic Puffin ([i]Fratercula arctica[/i]) is a species of seabird in the Auk family, one of 3 species of Puffins and the only one living in the northern Atlantic. It's recognizable by its large, ornate beak.

Atlantic Puffin (the Friend) is a large eater of snacks, usually seen eating a bag of chips. She typically refers to herself as "Puffin-chan". In Kemono Friends Pavilion, she is outright called "Puffin" in-game instead of her species name.

title: tanuki_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The Tanuki or "Raccoon Dog" ([i]Nyctereutes procyonoides[/i]) is, as its name suggests, a canid that ressembles a raccoon. It is native to East Asia and is well-documented in Japan, spawning [[inugami_gyoubu_(kemono_friends)|numerous]] [[danzaburou-danuki_(kemono_friends)|legends]] about it. It is considered to be a basal canid, distantly related to the true foxes.

Tanuki (the Friend) wears what is essentially a dark blue [[serafuku]] with fur-trimmed sleeves and a fur collar over the sailor collar. She has short, dark brown and white flipped hair that ressembles the "mask" of the original animal as well as brown eyes. Of course, she has the appropriate ears and tail.
other_names: タヌキ(けものフレンズ)

title: sophia_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Sophia[/b] (ソフィーヤ, [i]Sofiya[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]]. She is the Nabata Prophet, with the power to predict the future from the land of the same name (Nabata), and a half-dragon blooded girl. Her draconian blood makes her age slower than other humans.

In-game, Sophia is a dark-magic user of the Shaman class, with a great magic power and magic resistance, but poor speed and physical defense. Her initial low statistics and late appearance in the game makes her one of the most difficult characters to use.

She has [[absurdly long hair|absurdly long]] [[purple hair]] and [[purple eyes]], typically wears a [[cloak]], a [[blue dress|blue]] [[dress]] and a [[belly chain]].

title: felicia_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Felicia[/b] (フェリシア, [i]Ferishia[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

The maid who serves [[corrin (fire emblem)|Corrin]] (the Avatar) by doing all the tasks they need in the Kingdom of Nohr. While she is brave and tries her best, she still makes a lot of mistakes.

She is voiced by [[Sasaki Nozomi]] in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Maid

title: hans_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Hans[/b] (ガンズ, [i]Ganz[/i] in the Japanese version) is a character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Hans is a soldier of Nohr and a criminal who has committed a number of offenses. He has a lust for being successful in life, and uses his power to get what he wants.

He is voiced by Hisanori Koyatsu in the Japanese version and by Travis Willingham in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Berserker

title: hayato_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Hayato[/b] (ツクヨミ, [i]Tsukuyomi[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]]. 

A spellcaster of the Tribe of Winds. A young boy with extraordinary ability. This influences his self confidence, to the point where it is rather high-handed. On the other hand, his weakness is being childish in some ways, such as being afraid of the dark.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Spellcaster

title: candace_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Candace[/b] (ドラジェ, [i]Draj[/i] in the Japanese version) is a capturable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

She is the legendary genius explorer of Nohr. She has spent her entire life as an explorer.

She is voiced by Yuka Keicho in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Adventurer

title: charlotte_(fire_emblem)
body:
A playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

She is a mercenary of the border of the Kingdom of Nohr. She appears to be a truly kind girl to anyone who talks to her, but this is just a ruse to get any man under her control. Her true nature is that of a strong yet crude hand-to-hand fighter. She dreams of marrying into high wealth and social status.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[wavy hair|wavy]] [[blonde hair]], [[blue eyes]], [[large breasts]] and prominent [[lips]]. She wears a [[white bow|white]] [[hair bow|hair]] [[bow]] and a [[bikini armor|skimpy]] [[armor|armored]] outfit.

She is voiced by Shimizu Ai in the Japanese version and by Brianna Knickerbocker in the English localization. Her starting class is Fighter, making her the first female Fighter in the series.

title: azama_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Asama[/b] (アサマ, [i]Asama[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

[[hinoka (fire emblem)|Hinoka]]'s retainer. Sociable, he has a mild personality. Upon first glance he appears to be some kind of clergyman one can learn from. However, he is aloof from the world, questioning and thinking about menial such and such and is not afraid to show his sharp tongue.

He is voiced by [[Hamada Kenji]] in the Japanese version and by [[Matthew Mercer]] in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Monk -> Great Master

body: [b]Arete[/b] (シェンメイ, [i]Shenmei[/i]) is a now-dead character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]]. She was [[azura_(fire_emblem)|Azura]]'s mother and [[garon_(fire_emblem)|Garon]]'s second legal wife.

title: siegbert_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Siegbert[/b] (ジークベルト) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Seigbert is the son of [[xander_(fire_emblem)|Xander]] and the cousin of [[forrest_(fire_emblem)|Forrest]]. He is kind, serious, straightforward, and a culturally refined elite. He has the whitest teeth in the entire army.

He is voiced by Kengo Kawanishi in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Cavalier.

title: jane_maxwell
body:
Character in [i][[Wild Arms 1]][/i], also known as Calamity Jane. Jane also makes a cameo in [[Wild Arms 5]]. She is always seen with her butler [[Magdalen Harts]]. Her real name is Jane Maxwell, though she has no direct relation to [[Virginia Maxwell]], the protagonist of [i][[Wild Arms 3]][/i]. 'Calamity Jane' is a nickname based off a real historical figure named Martha Jane Cannary Burke.

Jane initially is a 'rival' to [[Rody Roughnight]]'s party as she hunts for treasure, but is actually trying to save her family orphanage in Court Seim. As she learns more about the group, she becomes friendlier with them and even develops feelings for Rody. While she joins the party in certain storyline moments, she can be picked up as a permanent member later.

In [i]Wild Arms 3[/i], [[Maya Schrodinger]] greatly resembles Jane, both in appearance and personality.  This is because Maya has the ability to mimic the abilities of characters from books she reads, and she particularly enjoys one called "Disaster Girl of the Wasteland," the title character of which is strongly implied to be Jane.

body:
A general term referring to the transformation items used in [[Kamen Rider OOO]]. The components that make up a Greeed and as a representation of desire and greed, O medals are classified in two categories: Core Medal and Cell Medal.

Core Medals are what makes up a Greeed and comes in three types: Head, Body, and Legs. These medals are what Hino Eiji uses to transform into [[Kamen Rider OOO]].

Cell Medals are the manifestation of human desire and make up the body of a Greeed and Yummy. These are used for the technology developed by the Kougami Foundation as well as the transformation item used by [[Kamen Rider Birth]]. 

For another explanation, the character Ankh explains that the medals are like a popsicle in the sense that Cells are what makes the ice cream part of a popsicle and Cores are the stick to keep it together.

title: boyd_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Boyd[/b] (ボーレ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Fighter (Path of Radiance), Warrior (Radiant Dawn).

He is the middle child of his family, and joined the Greil Mercenaries in order to support his younger brother [[Rolf (fire emblem)|Rolf]] and fight alongside his older brother [[Oscar (fire emblem)|Oscar]]. He is friendly rivals with [[ike (fire emblem)|Ike]] and is supervised occasionally by his Deputy Commander, [[Titania (fire emblem)|Titania]].

title: nealuchi_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Nealuchi[/b] (ニアルチ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

An elderly raven chamberlain and advisor to [[naesala (fire emblem)|Naesala]], Nealuchi fights to defeat Duke Ludveck's rebellion in Crimea. He is assigned to guard the Serenes Princess, [[leanne (fire emblem)|Leanne]], on behalf of his King and Prince [[reyson (fire emblem)|Reyson]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Raven

title: haar_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Haar[/b] (ハール) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] amd [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Haar was a member of Begnion's Holy Dracoknights, but later left with Shiharam as a result of being unable to tolerate the senate's corrupted ways.

Despite being a particularly lazy individual, Haar is an exceptional fighter.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wyvern Lord (Path of Radiance), Dragon Master (Radiant Dawn).

title: lucia_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Lucia[/b] (ルキノ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is a young lady descending from the house of Count Delbray the older sister of [[geoffrey_(fire_emblem)|Geoffrey]]  and the milk sister of [[elincia_ridell_crimea|Elincia]].  Lucia commands the Royal Guards with [[geoffrey_(fire_emblem)|Geoffrey]], and spearheads a clandestine network of spies to monitor the internal affairs of Crimea.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Swordmaster

title: geoffrey_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Geoffrey[/b]  is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is a Crimean general, and the commander of the Crimean Royal Knights. Geoffrey is the younger brother of [[lucia_(fire_emblem)|Lucia]], and is [[elincia_ridell_crimea|Elincia]]'s milk sibling and a close friend of [[Bastian (fire emblem)|Bastian]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Paladin (Path of Radiance), Lance Paladin (Radiant Dawn).

title: kieran_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Kieran[/b] (ケビン) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the sub-commander of the Crimean Royal Knights, and serves under General [[geoffrey_(fire_emblem)|Geoffrey]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Axe Knight (Path of Radiance), Axe Paladin (Radiant Dawn).

title: sigrun_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Sigrun[/b] (シグルーン) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is the commander of Begnion's Holy Guards, and serves directly underneath the Apostle [[sanaki_kirsch_altina|Sanaki]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Falcon Knight

title: pelleas_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Pelleas[/b] (ペレアス) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is believed to be the son of [[Ashnard (fire emblem)|Ashnard]] and the Prince of Daein. He has a strong devotion to his country and desires to free it from oppression by the Begnion Occupational Army. Pelleas acts as a figurehead for the Daein Liberation Army, which he entrusts [[micaiah (fire emblem)|Micaiah]] to lead in his stead as the commanding general.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Dark Sage

title: volug_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Volug[/b] (オルグ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Volug is Queen [[Nailah (fire emblem)|Nailah]]'s retainer. He is a Wolf Laguz, hailing from the lost nation of Hatari.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wolf

title: skrimir_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Skrimir[/b] (スクリミル) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the nephew of Gallia's King [[caineghis (fire emblem)|Caineghis]]. He commands the Laguz Alliance in the war with Begnion. He was named Caineghis' successor.

He is voiced by Tanzawa Teruyuki in the cutscenes.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Lion

title: rolf_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Rolf[/b] (ヨファ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the youngest member of the Greil Mercenaries and the younger brother of [[Oscar (fire emblem)|Oscar]] and [[Boyd (fire emblem)|Boyd]]. He is a mature, loyal young man. He was first taught how to use a bow by [[shinon_(fire_emblem)|Shinon]], so that, like [[mist_(fire_emblem)|Mist]], he could be of some use to the group rather than staying behind every time the company went to work.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Archer (Path of Radiance), Sniper (Radiant Dawn)

title: calill_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Calill[/b] (カリル) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is the wife of the Berserker [[largo_(fire_emblem)|Largo]] and a surrogate mother for their adopted child Amy. Calill and [[largo_(fire_emblem)|Largo]] also run a bar in Crimea, and are close friends with Queen [[elincia_ridell_crimea|Elincia]] and the Crimean Royal Knights.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Sage (Path of Radiance), Fire Sage (Radiant Dawn).

title: nolan_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Nolan[/b] (ノイス) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the official leader of the Dawn Brigade, although [[micaiah (fire emblem)|Micaiah]] usually acts as such throughout the story. He is the oldest member of the Dawn Brigade, and acts like a father figure to best friends [[edward_(fire_emblem)|Edward]] and [[leonardo_(fire_emblem)|Leonardo]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Fighter

title: vika_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Vika[/b] (ビーゼ, Vize) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Raven (Laguz)

h4. External links

title: muarim_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Muarim[/b] (ムワリム) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is a Tiger Laguz, and is a former slave of the Beorc race. Muarim acts as a father-figure and best friend to [[Tormod (fire emblem)|Tormod]] and fights the Begnion Occupational Army to liberate enslaved laguz.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Tiger.

title: fiona_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Fiona[/b] (フリーダ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is the daughter of Lanvega, who was one of Daein's Great Four Riders. She is the ruler of the independent Marado territory in Daein. At first, she sides with the Begnion Occupational Army, but later joins the Daein Liberation Army after seeing what kind of monstrous acts the Occupation Army does to her people. After the last battle, because she is the lady of Marado, she watched over her beloved people and would protect them until the autumn of her years.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Lance Knight

title: zihark_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Zihark[/b] (ツイハーク) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He was a citizen of Daein during The Mad King's War. Not much is known of Zihark's past, other than that he was born in Daein, and that he eventually fell in love with a Laguz of the Beast tribe Laguz, despite his homeland's prejudice towards the laguz. However, their relationship did not last, as the stress of being in a forbidden relationship proved too much for her

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Myrmidon (Path of Radiance), Swordmaster (Radiant Dawn).

title: tauroneo_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Tauroneo[/b] (タウロニオ) is a playable character that appears in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Tauroneo comes from a renowned military family in Daein. Tauroneo was once one of Daein's steadfast Four Riders. He shared that title with Gawain, Lanvega, and Bryce.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: General (Path of Radiance), Lance General (Radiant Dawn).

title: brom_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Brom[/b] (チャップ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He hails from the farming village of Ohma, which is also the hometown of [[Nephenee (fire emblem)|Nephenee]], and lives with a large family that consists of many children. Brom is the father of [[meg_(fire_emblem)|Meg]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Knight (Path of Radiance), Axe General (Radiant Dawn).

title: meg_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Meg[/b] (メグ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Meg is the daughter of [[brom (fire emblem)|Brom]]. Meg originally joins the Dawn Brigade hoping that she will 'meet her future husband' that her father told her to seek out.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Armor Sword

title: aran_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Aran[/b] (ブラッド) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He was initially a soldier fighting with the Begnion Occupational Army in Daein, but later joins the Dawn Brigade and the Daein Liberation Army.
Aran is a childhood friend of [[laura (fire emblem)|Laura]],having lived in Kisca with her for a good part of his early life.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Soldier

title: izana_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Izana[/b] (イザナ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Ruler of the Principality of Izumo. He has an unexpectedly cheerful and joking personality in contrast to his beautiful and divine appearance.

He is voiced by Toochika Kouichi in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Onmyoji

title: scarlet_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Scarlet[/b] (クリムゾン, [i]Crimson[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

The leader of the resistance in the Principality of Cheve opposing the Nohrian government. She has a pure, lively, freewheeling personality.

She is voiced by Ayano Ishikawa in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wyvern Lord

title: silas_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Silas[/b] (サイラス, [i]Sairasu[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

A new knight in the Kingdom of Nohr, and [[corrin (fire emblem)|Corrin]] (the Avatar)'s childhood friend. He has a kind heart and puts his friends before himself at all times. However, he is a very wary person as well, one who would sacrifice himself for an ally who had let their guard down.

He is voiced by Okumura Shou in the Japanese version and by Antony Del Rio in the English localization.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Cavalier

title: sophie_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Sophie[/b] (ゾフィー, Zofi) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Sophie is the daughter of [[silas_(fire_emblem)|Silas]]. Sophie is extremely prone to making mistakes, but is always optimistic and cheerful. She talks to herself more than anyone.

She is voiced by Sakura Nakamura in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Cavalier

title: my_room
body:
A [[gameplay_mechanics|gameplay mechanic]] in [[Fire Emblem Fates]] where the player character can play with their party members to increase relationship levels.

Using the touchscreen, the player can invite other members into their room and rub them.

h4. See also

* [[Pokemon-amie]], its pet/trainer equivalent

title: jakob_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Jakob[/b] (ジョーカー [i]Joker[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Serves as a steward to [[corrin (fire emblem)|Corrin]] (the Avatar) within the Kingdom of Nohr. He has keen intellect, and does everything from housework to odd jobs with great skill. However, he is rather unsociable to anybody who is not the Avatar.

He is voiced by [[Suwabe Jun'ichi]] in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Butler

title: dwyer_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Dwyer[/b] (ディーア, [i]Deere[/i] in the Japanese version) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

Deere is the son of [[jakob_(fire_emblem)|Jakob]]. Deere is normally seen competing against his father in some form or manner. Although lazy and apathetic, his motto is "work before rest". He is a naturally skilled butler and at combat. He has the most hidden talents.

He is voiced by Yuuichi Iguchi in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Rod Knight

title: lon'qu_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Lon'qu[/b] (ロンクー, [b]Ronku[/b] in the Japanese version, or [b]Lon'zu[/b] in the non-English European versions) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Awakening]].

A swordsman raised in Regna Ferox, where [[basilio (fire emblem)|Khan Basilio]] has vouched for his skill. While cool and curt around most people, the very sight of a woman turns him beet red. The deftest potato peeler. Born on October 10th.

He is voiced by [[Koyasu Takehito]] in the Japanese version and by Travis Willingham in the English localization.

title: laslow_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Laslow[/b] (ラズワルド, [i]Razuwarudo[/i]) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

A swordsman who serves [[xander (fire emblem)|Xander]]. He has a bright outgoing personality, and is friendly enough to mingle with anyone. He loves girls, and playing seducer in his free time seems to be enough for him. Dancing is his specialty.

He is voiced by Kijima Ryūichi in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Mercenary

h4. See also

* [[Inigo (Fire Emblem)]]

title: inigo_(fire_emblem)
body:
Second generation character in [[Fire Emblem Awakening]].

The son of [[olivia (fire emblem)|Olivia]]. Loves women, and takes the opportunity to try and flirt with them, often times unsuccessfully. He has a strong desire to be a dancer like his mother.

h4. See also

* [[Laslow (Fire Emblem)]]

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Archer

title: anna_(fire_emblem)
body:
A recurring money-obsessive female character in the [[Fire Emblem]] series. She is in every game except for [[Fire Emblem Gaiden]]. She is the operator of all secret shops found within the series and in [[Fire Emblem Awakening]] she was finally made into a playable character.

In all of her appearances she has [[long hair|long]] [[red hair]] in a [[ponytail]] and does the pose of [[light smile|lightly smiling]] with her [[finger to face|finger to her face]].

title: azura_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Azura[/b] (アクア Akua, Aqua) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

She is the opposite of [[corrin (fire emblem)|Corrin]] (the Avatar), having been born in Nohr but kidnapped and raised in Hoshido. After she meets the protagonist, she travels with them no matter what choice they make. She holds a special power in the songs she sings.

She is voiced by Lynn in the Japanese version. Her singing voice is provided by Renka. In the English localization, Rena Strober provides both her voice acting and singing.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Songstress

title: shigure_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Shigure[/b] (シグレ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

He is the son of [[azura_(fire_emblem)|Azura]] and inherited her beautiful singing voice. Shigure has a natural love for the arts and is especially fond of singing like his mother. He loves high places.

He is voiced by Yoshimasa Hosoya in the Japanese version.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Pegasus Warrior

title: subaki_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Subaki[/b] (ツバキ, Tsubaki) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

He rides a pegasus as [[sakura (fire emblem)|Sakura]]'s subordinate. He's always smiling and has an easygoing demeanor. Although it seems like he takes things too lightly, he has another side inside that strives for perfection.

title: moped
body:
A type of low-powered [[motorcycle]] that uses bicycle pedals to assist the engine with hill-climbing and pedaling away from a stationary position. The term [i]moped[/i] originates from the Swedish words [i][b]mo[/b]tor[/i] and [i][b]ped[/b]aler[/i]. Some mopeds have a step-through design (post #1132037) while others use a conventional motorcycle frame (post #689998). At the lighter end of the scale, there is some overlap between mopeds and motorized [[bicycle|bicycles]].

Some regional governments classify motor scooters as mopeds based on factors such as engine displacement or speed. As these rules vary between jurisdictions and vehicle performance can not always be ascertained based on artwork, two-wheeled motor vehicles with a step-through design but without pedals should always be tagged [[scooter]] instead.

title: king_dedede
body:
King Dedede is the self-proclaimed king of Dream Land, [[kirby|Kirby's]] #1 rival, and a recurring antagonist in the [i][[kirby_(series)|Kirby]][/i] games. Typically caring only for himself, he likes to mess with others because he thinks it's fun. He even once stole all of Dream Land's food. However, Dedede isn't all bad - he's just more of a bully who pulls pranks on others just for the fun of it. Sometimes, he does do good deeds, and will even team up with Kirby more often than he'd like to admit.

In the [[kirby:_right_back_at_ya|anime]], Dedede also pulls pranks on others and especially tries to make other people's lives as miserable as he can because he thinks it's fun. He buys monsters called [[Demon Beast|Demon Beasts]] created by the Holy Nightmare Company, led by [[Nightmare_(Kirby)|Nightmare]], to help him with his desires, and has a snail sidekick called [[Escargon]].

title: c2_kikan
body:
C2 Kikan (Japanese: C2機関/株式会社C2プレパラート (C2 Präparat Inc.)), alternatively translated as "C2 Architecture", "Contents Communication Architecture", and aka "KanColle Unei Chinjufu", is a doujin circle, who is one of the copyright holders of the [[Kantai Collection]] -KanColle- brand.

C2 Kikan debuted in Comiket C75 (Winter 2008) with a doujin about food, introducing various types of food through anime personifications. They were interviewed by various TV programs for it at the time, including タモリ倶楽部 from Asahi TV and MAG・ネット from NHK. They later published several military-related doujinshi.

It's possible that the name of 'C2 Kikan' came from Final Fantasy: Unlimited, where Tanaka Kensuke, one of the main members of C2 Kikan, was the anime's general producer for, when he worked in Square Soft back in 2001.

When Tanaka Kensuke and his friend, who was working within Kadokawa Games talked with Michio Okamiya, whom he once worked with back in Square Soft, they came up with the idea of the KanColle browser game.

(Source: "KanColle Wiki":https://kancolle.fandom.com/wiki/C2_Kikan)

Official website: http://www.c2architecture.com/
Official twitter: https://twitter.com/C2_STAFF

title: jack_daniel's
body:
Jack Daniel's is a brand of Tennessee whiskey and the top-selling American whiskey in the world. It is produced in Lynchburg, Tennessee, by the Jack Daniel Distillery, which has been owned by the Brown–Forman Corporation since 1956.

Packaged in square bottles, Jack Daniel's "Black Label" Tennessee whiskey sold 12.5 million cases in 2017. Other brand variations, such as Tennessee Honey, Gentleman Jack, and Tennessee Fire, added another 2.9 million cases to sales. Sales of an additional 800,000 equivalent cases in ready-to-drink (RTD) products brought the fiscal year total to more than 16.1 million equivalent adjusted cases for the entire Jack Daniel's family of brands. 

Jack Daniel's home county of Moore is a dry county, so the product is not available for purchase at stores or restaurants within the county.

title: shigofumi
body:
Shigofumi (シゴフミ ~Stories of Last Letter~) is a series of 12 episodes fantasy anime directed by Tatsuo Satou, aired between January and March 2008. There's also a light novel of the same series, released before the anime in October 2006, but considered a consequent work, as the project of this anime has afore been commenced.

The story, as titled, focuses on supernatural events that occurs on many dead people who reached afterlife, which allow them to send something, mostly letters that contain unexpressed feeling when they were alive, to anyone in the living world via "shigofumi." Dead youths in uniform, each wielding an AI implemented staff as aid granter, are used in carrying tasks. To every individual carrier has their own specific area of work on the world but shares the same workplace when not out for delivering, in another realm called Shigo.

Fumika, a young early teenage girl and the female protagonist, takes part in the story as another carrier of shigofumi. She hides her past behind from her little society, but the only thing that remains obviously doubtful is her normally flowing age, which is supposed to stop when she died and became a shigofumi carrier, like every others.

title: suikawari
body:
Suikawari (lit. [i][[watermelon]] splitting[/i]) is a traditional Japanese game which usually takes place at the [[beach]] during the [[summer|summertime]]. It is similar to the Western party game of hitting a piñata: players are given a bat or stick, [[blindfold|blindfolded]] and spun around three times, then attempt to strike the watermelon. Whoever cracks the watermelon first wins and afterwards the remains of the watermelon are shared with all participants of the game.

Might also involve a [[pun]] involving [[Ibuki Suika]] of the Touhou series being hit on the head, somewhat based off a line in Yuyuko in one of the games about going "Suika Bashing" when fighting her.
